        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued September 6 at 10:12PM EDT until September 7 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High wave action, strong currents, and dangerous
swimming conditions expected. Piers will be heavily swamped by
waves.

* WHERE...Northern Berrien and Southern Berrien counties.

* WHEN...Through Sunday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
